claim.claim-text:
1. Drive device for adjusting an operating element in a component used in the field of gas or oil exploitation and/or production, comprising:
driving motors;
a drive train actively connecting the operating element with the driving motors, the drive train comprising:
at least two drive shafts, each drive shaft comprising a worm gear arranged essentially centrically on the drive shaft and each respective drive shaft rotatable by separate driving motors at each end;
at least one worm wheel actively connected with and rotated by the at least two drive shafts; and
at least one transmission changing unit driven by the at least one worm wheel for converting a revolution of the driving motors into a revolution of the operating element and comprising a step-down gear unit.

8. Drive device for adjusting an operating element in a component used in the field of gas or oil exploitation and/or production, comprising:
driving motors;
a drive train actively connecting the driving motors and the operating element and comprising:
at least two drive shafts, each drive shaft comprising a worm gear arranged essentially centrically on the drive shaft and each respective drive shaft rotatable by separate driving motors on each end;
at least one worm wheel actively connected with and driven b the at least two drive shafts;
at least one transmission changing unit driven by the at least one worm wheel for converting a revolution of the driving motor into a revolution of the operating element; and a revolution/linear motion converter being arranged for converting the revolution of the driving motor into a linear motion of the operating element and comprising a step-down gear unit.
